title: Says I dont have at least 20 Champs (to play ranked)
body: So I just bought (what i thought to be) my 20th champion in league of legends so i could finally start playing some ranked. But for some reason (idk if its a glitch or im missing something or what) it is still saying that i dont have twenty champs yet, but im fairly confident that i do (akali, amumu, annie, ashe, cho'gath, garen, kayle, master yi, mordekaiser, morgana, nasus, nanu, poppy, ryze, shyvana, singed, sivir, soraka, tryndamere, and warwick... thats 20 right?) Can someone tell me whats going on or, better yet, everything that i need in order to play ranked? I must be missing something. THANKS!!

replies.body: Ayyyy glad Kokua was able to point that out! Always good to give that client a rest when you aren't using it!
Nunu is too garbage to be considered a champion.

If you just purchased it recently, you might want to restart your client and see if it syncs up. I'm not sure if this number is inclusive of free champion rotation or exclusive. Amumu seems to be the only champion that you listed that is also on the [current free rotation](https://na.leagueoflegends.com/en/news/champions-skins/free-rotation), so are you sure that you own him?
Yup that would be it. I restarted my client and it worked. Thanks for the help!

Considering the free champion rotation isn't (to my knowledge) included in ranked selections, I believe the requirement is to own 20 champions independent of the free week ones. Free week champions you *own* will be included, but free week champions you do not own will not.
